title: Too High
lyrics:
[Intro]
Do-do, do, do, do, do-do
Do-do, do-do, do, do-do
Do-do, do-do, do, do
Do-do, do, do, do, do-do
Do, do, do, do, do-do, do
Do-do, do-do, do-do
[Chorus]
I'm too high, I'm too high
But I ain't touched the sky
I'm too high, I'm too high
But I ain't touched the sky
[Verse 1]
She's a girl in a dream
She sees a four-eyed cartoon monster on the T.V. screen
She takes another puff, and says, "It's a crazy scene"
That red is green
And she's a tangerine
[Chorus]
I'm too high, I'm too high
But I ain't left the ground
I'm too high, I'm too high
I hope I never ever come down

[Verse 2]
She's the girl in her life
But her world's a 
superficial paradise
She had a chance to make it big more than once or twice
But, no dice
She wasn't very nice
Ow!
[Refrain]
Do-do, do, do, do, do-do (Do...)
Do, do, do-do, do, do-do (Oh... oh...)
Do, do, do, do, do, do (Oh... oh... hey!)
[Instrumental Break 1: Harmonica Solo]
[Refrain]
Do-do, do-do, do-do-do
Do, do, do-do, do-do-do
Do-do, do-do, do-do, do-do, do-do, do-do
[Chorus]
I'm too high, I'm too high
I can't ever touch the sky
I'm too high, I'm so high
I feel like I'm about to die

[Verse 3]
She's a girl of the past
I guess that all got to her at last
Ah, did you hear the news about the girl today?
She passed away
What did her friends say?
[Instrumental Break 2: Moog Solo]
[Chorus]
They said she's too high, too high
Can't hang around her anyway...
[Outro]
Do-do, do, do, do, do-do
Do-do, do, do, do, do-do
Do, do, do
Do, do, do
Do-do-do-do-do, do-do-do
